                <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/2415: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Arica</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Von Tresckow</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-06-08T23:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 8, 1926—11 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>For Lassiter. My telegram June 8, 7 p.m. After further reflection and
                    consideration of latest advices from Santiago, I am disposed to allow you to use
                    your own judgment and proceed with introduction of your resolution unless
                    Edwards relieves you of embarrassment by consenting to maintain <hi
                        rend="italic">status quo</hi> for such further period as may be agreed upon.
                    Of course we are anxious to save every possible chance for settlement by
                    negotiation. It is only because Ambassador Cruchaga insists that such a chance
                    exists that we have urged you to find some way for a further postponement, but
                    we do not wish you to construe these messages as a direction to you to postpone
                    it in face of further protests from Chilean Commissioner.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
